text:
ordered basil pork belly with rice, food came with no color at all. asked the server “no basil in the basil pork?” and he responded “ya”

don’t know whether to laugh or cry

Food:
Green curry $12.90: it's quite flavourful yet not to spicy. It's good for those that like green curry but aren't good with spice. Sizewise it's just nice for 1 person. Wished they added more chicken and less mushroom and also if the Thai basil was cut into strips and instead just left whole as it really is annoying to remove it while eating 3/5

Basil chicken rice $7.90: Chicken is very flavourful and tasty about. The portion given was fair for 7.90. comes with free small milk tea. 5/5

Service: food came out decently fast but granted I went when no one was ard

Atmosphere: It's chill
Food took a while to be served even though place was not very crowded. Just had my family and another group. Food was okay but could do better.
Great thai food with a cosy environment.. recommended chilled place to enjoy taste of Thailand!
Good mains. Moo ping was juicy, egg fried rice was tasty and had lots of vegetables.
